{"title_page": "Afsana Mimi", "text_new": "{{short description|Bengali actress, filmmaker (born 1968)}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name             = Afsana Mimi\n| image            = AFSANA MIMI IN 2017.jpg\n| caption          = Mimi in 2017\n| native_name      = \u0986\u09ab\u09b8\u09be\u09a8\u09be \u09ae\u09bf\u09ae\u09bf\n| native_name_lang = bangla\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1968|12|20|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Dhaka]], [[East Pakistan]], Pakistan now [[Bangladesh]]\n| nationality      = Bangladeshi\n| education        = [[English Literature]]\n| alma_mater       = [[University of Dhaka]]\n| occupation       = Actress, model, script-writer, television director\n| years_active     = 1990-present\n| spouse           = {{marriage|[[Gazi Rakayet]]|1995|1996|end=div}}\n| mother           = Shirin Afroze\n| father           = Syed Fazlul Karim\n}}\n'''Afsana Mimi''' (born 20 December 1968)<ref name=tradition>{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/tv/afsana-mimi-has-special-birthday-tradition-1332481|title=Afsana Mimi has a special birthday tradition|date=December 20, 2016|accessdate=February 20, 2017|newspaper=The Daily Star|author=Shah Alam Shazu}}</ref><ref name=birthday>{{citenews|url=http://news.priyo.com/tv/2011/12/20/birthday-celebrations-mimi-and-44351.html |title=Birthday celebrations for Mimi and Nobel |newspaper=Priyo News |date=December 20, 2011 |accessdate=October 17, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222164125/http://news.priyo.com/tv/2011/12/20/birthday-celebrations-mimi-and-44351.html |archivedate=December 22, 2015 }}</ref> is a Bangladeshi actress, model and director.<ref name=dstar>{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/beta2/news/bipasha-shomi-mimi-where-do-they-stand-now/|title=Bipasha, Shomi & Mimi\u2026 Where do they stand now?|publisher=The Daily Star|date=September 28, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nMimi was born on 20 December 1968 at Holy Family Hospital, [[Dhaka]] in the then [[East Pakistan]].<ref name=tradition/>\n\n== Career ==\nMimi started her acting career through the theater troupe [[Nagorik Natya Sampradaya]].<ref name=birthday/> Her last play was Prachyanat's ''Raja Ebong Onnanno'' in 2011.<ref name=tola>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/interview/news/afsana-mimis-hopes-ichchhetola-1653427|title=Afsana Mimi's hopes for Ichchhetola|date=2018-10-30|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2019-11-20}}</ref> Mimi got her breakthrough in acting in Bengali television drama ''[[Kothao Keu Nei]]'' in 1990.<ref name=mimi/> Her acting in Nokkhotrer Raat was amazing.\n\nMimi started directing in 2000.<ref name=mimi>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/afsana-mimi-37128|title=AFSANA MIMI|date=2014-08-16|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2019-11-20}}</ref> She directed ''Kaacher Manush''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/bangla/anandadhara/%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9B%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%9C%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%9F-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9C%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%85%E0%A6%A5%E0%A6%9A-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%9C%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%9F-%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%87-126262|title=\u2018\u09b8\u09ac\u0995\u09bf\u099b\u09c1\u09b0 \u09ac\u09be\u099c\u09c7\u099f \u09ac\u09be\u09a1\u09bc\u09c7 \u0985\u09a5\u099a \u09a8\u09be\u099f\u0995\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ac\u09be\u099c\u09c7\u099f \u0995\u09ae\u09c7\u2019|date=2019-11-19|website=The Daily Star Bangla|language=bn|access-date=2019-11-20}}</ref> She worked on a cooking show on ATN News named ''Nostalgia''.<ref name=mimi/>\n\nMimi serves as the director of ''Ichchhetola'', a cultural centre in Dhaka.<ref name=tola/>Lately she anchored a talk-show ''Moner Kotha''. She owns a production house named \"Krishnachura<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/magazine/2010/09/01/cover.htm|title=::: Star Weekend Magazine :::|website=www.thedailystar.net|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\".\n[[File:Afsanamimi.jpg|alt=|thumb|325x325px|Afsana Mimi Young]]\n<gallery widths=\"200\" heights=\"200\">\nFile:Afsanamimi kothao keu nei.jpg|kishor tarokaloke rokashito afsana mimi and shila ahmed (''[[Kothao Keu Nei]]'')\nFile:Afsanamimi Dil.jpg|Afsana mimi in Dil Movie\nFile:Afsanamimi Advertisement.jpg|advertisement in early 90s\nFile:Afsanamimi Advertisement young.jpg|Advertisements\nFile:Afsanamimi chitra nodir pare.jpg|Afsana mimi in ''[[Chitra Nodir Pare]]'' Movie\nFile:Afsanakarimmimi.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n\n== Works ==\n===Films===\n;Acting\n* ''[[Nodir Naam Modhumoti]]'' (1996)\n* ''[[Chitra Nodir Pare]]'' / Quiet Flows the River Chitra(1999)\n* ''Priyotomeshu'' (2009)\n*Bihango\n*Liliputra Boro Hobe\n*Chana o Muktijuddho\n*Dil (commercial film)\n\n=== Television ===\n;Acting\n\n*\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|'''Year'''\n|'''TV series and TV films'''\n|'''Director & Playwright'''\n|'''Co-stars'''\n|'''Notes'''\n|-\n|1990\n|''[[Kothao Keu Nei]]'' [[Kothao Keu Nei|(1990)]]<ref>{{cite news|author=Mohammad Zahidul Islam|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/afsana-mimi-37128|title=Afsana Mimi|date=August 16, 2014|newspaper=The Daily Star|accessdate=October 17, 2015}}</ref>\n|Humayun Ahmed\n|Suborna  Mustafa, Humayun Faridi, Abul Hayat\n|Drama  serial, aired on BTV\n|-\n|\n|Nokkhotrer Raat\n|Humayun Ahmed\n|Abul Khayer, Abul Hayat, Dilara Zaman, Aly Zaker, Sara Zaker, \nAsaduzzaman Noor, Dr. Enamul Haque, Lucky Enam, Abdul Quader, \n\nAzizul Hakim, Jahid Hasan, Meher Afroz Shaon, Shila Ahmed, Bipasha Ahmed,\n\nShomi Kaiser, Afsana Mimi, Saleh Uddin Ahmed, \n|Drama  serial, aired on BTV\n|-\n|\n|Kotha  Dilam\n|\n|Tony  Dayes\n|2nd  part \"Shei Tumi\"\n|-\n|\n|Sabuj Sathi\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|\n|Bandhan\n|\n|Jahid  Hasan\n|\n|-\n|\n|Kakhano  Shomoy Ashe\n|\n|Tony  Dayes\n|\n|-\n|\n|Nila  Namer Meyeti\n|\n|Tony  Dayes\n|\n|-\n|\n|Jiban  Jemon\n|\n|Zahid  Hasan\n|\n|-\n|\n|Shei  Tumi\n|\n|Tony  Dayes\n|1st  Part \"Kotha Dilam\"\n|-\n|\n|Shesh 